Text which displays under a property in the Properties widget if the property is being influenced by another Instance. 'Influenced', in this case, means that the property's value will only be set by the other Instance under certain circumstances (e.g. a UISizeConstraint clamping a UI element's Size property down if it exceeds a certain maximum).

description: Text which displays under a property in the Properties widget if the property is being overridden by another Instance. 'Overridden', in this case, means that the property's value will always be set by the other Instance regardless of what the user sets the property's value to in the Properties widget (e.g. a UIGridLayout always overriding a UI element's Size and Position properties).

Tooltip that displays if a certain Instance's property is being influenced by another Instance(s). Parameter 1 is the name of the Instance whose property is being altered, parameter 2 is the name of the property being altered, and parameter 3 is the name(s) of the Instance(s) that is/are altering the property. 'Influenced', in this case, means that the property's value will only be set by the other Instance(s) under certain circumstances (i.e. a UISizeConstraint clamping a UI element's size down if it exceeds a certain maximum).

Tooltip that displays if a certain Instance's property is being overridden by another Instance(s). Parameter 1 is the name of the Instance whose property is being altered, parameter 2 is the name of the property being altered, and parameter 3 is the name(s) of the Instance(s) that is/are altering the property. 'Overridden', in this case, means that the property's value will always be set by the other instance(s) regardless of what the user sets the property's value to in the Properties widget.

english: The viewport's (game window) height in pixels.
translation: The viewport's (game window) height in pixels.

english: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the x-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the left hand side of the screen and increase to the right.
translation: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the x-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the left hand side of the screen and increase to the right.

english: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the y-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the top of the screen and increase to the bottom.
translation: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the y-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the top of the screen and increase to the bottom.

english: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is depressed.
translation: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is depressed.

english: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is release.
translation: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is release.

english: Fired constantly when the mouse is not firing any other event (i.e. the mouse isn't moving, nor any buttons being pressed or depressed).
translation: Fired constantly when the mouse is not firing any other event (i.e. the mouse isn't moving, nor any buttons being pressed or depressed).

english: Fired when a user presses a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
translation: Fired when a user presses a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.

english: Fired when a user releases a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
translation: Fired when a user releases a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.

english: Fired when the mouse X or Y member changes.
translation: Fired when the mouse X or Y member changes.

english: Raises mouse events for parent object
translation: Raises mouse events for parent object

english: The maximum distance a Player's character can be from the ClickDetector's parent Part that will allow the Player's mouse to fire events on this object.
translation: The maximum distance a Player's character can be from the ClickDetector's parent Part that will allow the Player's mouse to fire events on this object.

english: Fired when a player clicks on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
translation: Fired when a player clicks on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.

english: Fired when a player's mouse enters on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
translation: Fired when a player's mouse enters on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.

english: Fired when a player's mouse leaves the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
translation: Fired when a player's mouse leaves the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.

english: Makes the parent part or model object emit smoke
translation: Makes the parent part or model object emit smoke

english: Makes two attachments emit trail when moving
translation: Makes two attachments emit trail when moving

english: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the particle emmitter. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
translation: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the particle emmitter. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

english: Makes the parent part or model object fantastic
translation: Makes the parent part or model object fantastic

english: Creates an Explosion! This can be used as a purely graphical effect, or can be made to damage objects.
translation: Creates an Explosion! This can be used as a purely graphical effect, or can be made to damage objects.

english: How much force this Explosion exerts on objects within it's BlastRadius. Setting this to 0 creates a purely graphical effect. A larger number will cause Parts to fly away at higher velocities.
translation: How much force this Explosion exerts on objects within it's BlastRadius. Setting this to 0 creates a purely graphical effect. A larger number will cause Parts to fly away at higher velocities.

english: How big the Explosion is. This is a circle starting from the center of the Explosion's Position, the larger this property the larger the circle of destruction.
translation: How big the Explosion is. This is a circle starting from the center of the Explosion's Position, the larger this property the larger the circle of destruction.

english: Where the Explosion occurs in absolute world coordinates.
translation: Where the Explosion occurs in absolute world coordinates.

english: Defines the behavior of the Explosion. More info
translation: Defines the behavior of the Explosion. More info

english: Makes the parent part or model object emit fire
translation: Makes the parent part or model object emit fire

english: The color of the base of the fire.  See SecondaryColor for more.
translation: The color of the base of the fire.  See SecondaryColor for more.

english: How hot the fire appears to be. The flame moves quicker the higher this value is set.
translation: How hot the fire appears to be. The flame moves quicker the higher this value is set.

english: The color the fire interpolates to from Color. The longer a particle exists in the fire, the close to this color it becomes.
translation: The color the fire interpolates to from Color. The longer a particle exists in the fire, the close to this color it becomes.

english: How large the fire appears to be.
translation: How large the fire appears to be.

english: Equivalent to a seat, except that the character stands up rather than sits down.
translation: Equivalent to a seat, except that the character stands up rather than sits down.

english: Automatically finds and powers hinge joints in an assembly.  Ignores motors.
translation: Automatically finds and powers hinge joints in an assembly.  Ignores motors.

english: If someone is carrying this flag, this bool determines whether or not they can drop it and run.
translation: If someone is carrying this flag, this bool determines whether or not they can drop it and run.

english: The Team this flag is for. Corresponds with the TeamColors in the Teams service.
translation: The Team this flag is for. Corresponds with the TeamColors in the Teams service.

english: Descibes a texture that is placed on one of the sides of the Part it is parented to.
translation: Descibes a texture that is placed on one of the sides of the Part it is parented to.

english: Describes the face of the Part the decal will be applied to. More info
translation: Describes the face of the Part the decal will be applied to. More info

english: How much light will appear to reflect off of the decal.
translation: How much light will appear to reflect off of the decal.

english: How light will react to the surface of the decal.
translation: How light will react to the surface of the decal.

english: How visible the decal is.  1 is completely invisible, while 0 is completely opaque
translation: How visible the decal is.  1 is completely invisible, while 0 is completely opaque

english: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.
translation: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.

english: Stores a int value in it's Value member. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a int value in it's Value member. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.

english: Stores a Ray value in it's Value member. Useful to share Ray information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a Ray value in it's Value member. Useful to share Ray information across multiple scripts.

english: Stores an int value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores an int value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.

english: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
translation: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue

english: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
translation: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue

english: Stores a double value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share double information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a double value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share double information across multiple scripts.

english: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
translation: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue

english: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
translation: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue

english: Stores a boolean value in it's Value member. Useful to share boolean information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a boolean value in it's Value member. Useful to share boolean information across multiple scripts.

english: Renders a thin cylinder than can be adorned with textures that 'flow' from one object to the next. Has basic pathing abilities and attempts to to not intersect anything. More info
translation: Renders a thin cylinder than can be adorned with textures that 'flow' from one object to the next. Has basic pathing abilities and attempts to to not intersect anything. More info

english: Controls how the decals are positioned along the wire. More info
translation: Controls how the decals are positioned along the wire. More info

english: The space between two textures on the wire. Note: studs are relative depending on how far the camera is from the FloorWire.
translation: The space between two textures on the wire. Note: studs are relative depending on how far the camera is from the FloorWire.

english: The image we use to render the textures that flow from beginning to end of the FloorWire.
translation: The image we use to render the textures that flow from beginning to end of the FloorWire.

english: The size in studs of the Texture we use to flow from one object to the next.
translation: The size in studs of the Texture we use to flow from one object to the next.

english: The rate of travel that the textures flow along the wire.
translation: The rate of travel that the textures flow along the wire.

english: Stores a CFrame value in it's Value member. Useful to share CFrame information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a CFrame value in it's Value member. Useful to share CFrame information across multiple scripts.

english: Stores a Color3 value in it's Value member. Useful to share Color3 information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a Color3 value in it's Value member. Useful to share Color3 information across multiple scripts.

english: Stores a BrickColor value in it's Value member. Useful to share BrickColor information across multiple scripts.
translation: Stores a BrickColor value in it's Value member. Useful to share BrickColor information across multiple scripts.

english: The base class to all Value Objects.
translation: The base class to all Value Objects.

english: The sound will play when it is removed from the Workspace. Looped sounds don't play
translation: The sound will play when it is removed from the Workspace. Looped sounds don't play

english: An echo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: An echo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Flanging audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Flanging audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Distortion audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Distortion audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Pitch Shifting audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Pitch Shifting audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Chorus audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Chorus audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Tremolo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Tremolo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Reverb audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Reverb audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: An Three-band Equalizer audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: An Three-band Equalizer audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: A Compressor audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
translation: A Compressor audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

english: The ambient sound environment.  May not work when using hardware sound
translation: The ambient sound environment.  May not work when using hardware sound

english: The doppler scale is a general scaling factor for how much the pitch varies due to doppler shifting in 3D sound. Doppler is the pitch bending effect when a sound comes towards the listener or moves away from it, much like the effect you hear when a train goes past you with its horn sounding. With dopplerscale you can exaggerate or diminish the effect.
translation: The doppler scale is a general scaling factor for how much the pitch varies due to doppler shifting in 3D sound. Doppler is the pitch bending effect when a sound comes towards the listener or moves away from it, much like the effect you hear when a train goes past you with its horn sounding. With dopplerscale you can exaggerate or diminish the effect.

english: the relative distance factor, compared to 1.0 meters.
translation: the relative distance factor, compared to 1.0 meters.

english: Setting this value makes the sound drop off faster or slower. The higher the value, the faster volume will attenuate, and conversely the lower the value, the slower it will attenuate. For example a rolloff factor of 1 will simulate the real world, where as a value of 2 will make sounds attenuate 2 times quicker.
translation: Setting this value makes the sound drop off faster or slower. The higher the value, the faster volume will attenuate, and conversely the lower the value, the slower it will attenuate. For example a rolloff factor of 1 will simulate the real world, where as a value of 2 will make sounds attenuate 2 times quicker.

english: When SortOrder is set to Custom, this lua function is used to determine the ordering of elements. Function should take two arguments (each will be an Instance child to compare), and return true if a comes before b, otherwise return false. In other words, use this function the same way you would use a table.sort function. The sorting should be deterministic, otherwise sort will fail and fall back to name order.
translation: When SortOrder is set to Custom, this lua function is used to determine the ordering of elements. Function should take two arguments (each will be an Instance child to compare), and return true if a comes before b, otherwise return false. In other words, use this function the same way you would use a table.sort function. The sorting should be deterministic, otherwise sort will fail and fall back to name order.

english: Forces a relayout of all elements. Useful when sort is set to Custom.
translation: Forces a relayout of all elements. Useful when sort is set to Custom.

english: Determines how we decide which element to place next. Can be Name or Custom. If using Custom, make sure SetCustomSortFunction was called with an appropriate sort function.
translation: Determines how we decide which element to place next. Can be Name or Custom. If using Custom, make sure SetCustomSortFunction was called with an appropriate sort function.

english: Determines which direction to fill the grid. Can be Horizontal or Vertical.
translation: Determines which direction to fill the grid. Can be Horizontal or Vertical.

english: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the x direction. Can be Left, Center, or Right.
translation: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the x direction. Can be Left, Center, or Right.

english: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the y direction. Can be Top, Center, or Bottom.
translation: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the y direction. Can be Top, Center, or Bottom.

english: Sets the position of UI elements in a list. You can use a UIListLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
translation: Sets the position of UI elements in a list. You can use a UIListLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

english: Determines the amount of free space between each element. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
translation: Determines the amount of free space between each element. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).

english: Sets the position of UI elements inline. You can use a UIInlineLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
translation: Sets the position of UI elements inline. You can use a UIInlineLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

english: Sets the position of UI elements in a 2D grid (this can be modified to 1D grid for list layout). This will also set the elements to a particular size, although this can be overridden with particular constraints on elements. You can use a UIGridLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIGridLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
translation: Sets the position of UI elements in a 2D grid (this can be modified to 1D grid for list layout). This will also set the elements to a particular size, although this can be overridden with particular constraints on elements. You can use a UIGridLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIGridLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

english: Denotes what size each element should be. Can be overridden by elements using constraints on individual elements.
translation: Denotes what size each element should be. Can be overridden by elements using constraints on individual elements.

english: How much space between elements there should be.
translation: How much space between elements there should be.

english: Determines how many cells over in the FillDirection we go before starting a new row or column. Set to 0 for max cell count.  Will be clamped if this is set higher than the parent container allows room for.
translation: Determines how many cells over in the FillDirection we go before starting a new row or column. Set to 0 for max cell count.  Will be clamped if this is set higher than the parent container allows room for.

english: Returns the current size of the grid. If more elements are added, this can increase. If elements are removed this can decrease.
translation: Returns the current size of the grid. If more elements are added, this can increase. If elements are removed this can decrease.

english: Which corner we start laying the elements out from. Can be TopLeft, TopRight, BottomLeft, BottomRight.
translation: Which corner we start laying the elements out from. Can be TopLeft, TopRight, BottomLeft, BottomRight.

english: Creates a paged viewing window, like the home screen of a mobile device. You can use a UIPageLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIPageLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
translation: Creates a paged viewing window, like the home screen of a mobile device. You can use a UIPageLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIPageLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

english: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.
translation: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.

english: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.
translation: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.

english: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
translation: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).

english: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.
translation: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.

english: The easing style to use when performing an animation.
translation: The easing style to use when performing an animation.

english: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.
translation: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.

english: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
translation: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.

english: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
translation: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.

english: If the instance is in the layout, then it sets CurrentPage to it and animtes to it. If circular layout is set, it will take the shortest path.
translation: If the instance is in the layout, then it sets CurrentPage to it and animtes to it. If circular layout is set, it will take the shortest path.

english: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, acts like JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of CurrentPage and the new index.
translation: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, acts like JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of CurrentPage and the new index.

english: Fires when a page comes into view, and is going to be rendered.
translation: Fires when a page comes into view, and is going to be rendered.

english: Fires when a page leaves view, and will not be rendered.
translation: Fires when a page leaves view, and will not be rendered.

english: Fires when an animation to CurrentPage is completed without being cancelled, and the view stops scrolling.
translation: Fires when an animation to CurrentPage is completed without being cancelled, and the view stops scrolling.

english: Provides a layout of rows and columns that are sized based on the cells in them.
translation: Provides a layout of rows and columns that are sized based on the cells in them.

english: The amount of padding to insert in between the cells of the table.
translation: The amount of padding to insert in between the cells of the table.

english: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, row-wise.
translation: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, row-wise.

english: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, column-wise.
translation: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, column-wise.

english: Whether the direct siblings are considered the rows or the columns. The children of the direct siblings are the columns or rows, respectively.
translation: Whether the direct siblings are considered the rows or the columns. The children of the direct siblings are the columns or rows, respectively.

english: Ensures a GuiObject does not become smaller or larger than the min and max size. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
translation: Ensures a GuiObject does not become smaller or larger than the min and max size. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.

english: The smallest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
translation: The smallest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.

english: The biggest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
translation: The biggest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.

english: Ensures a GuiObject with text does not allow the font size to become larger or smaller than min and max text sizes. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
translation: Ensures a GuiObject with text does not allow the font size to become larger or smaller than min and max text sizes. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.

english: The smallest size the font is allowed to be.
translation: The smallest size the font is allowed to be.

english: The biggest size the font is allowed to be.
translation: The biggest size the font is allowed to be.

english: Ensures a GuiObject will always have a particular aspect ratio. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
translation: Ensures a GuiObject will always have a particular aspect ratio. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.

english: The aspect ratio to maintain. This is the width/height. Only positive numbers allowed.
translation: The aspect ratio to maintain. This is the width/height. Only positive numbers allowed.

english: Describes how the aspect ratio will determine its size. Options are FitWithinMaxSize, ScaleWithParentSize. FitWithinMaxSize will make the element the maximum size it can be within the current possible AbsoluteSize of the element while maintaining the AspectRatio. ScaleWithParentSize will make the element the closest to the parent element’s maximum size while maintaining aspect ratio.
translation: Describes how the aspect ratio will determine its size. Options are FitWithinMaxSize, ScaleWithParentSize. FitWithinMaxSize will make the element the maximum size it can be within the current possible AbsoluteSize of the element while maintaining the AspectRatio. ScaleWithParentSize will make the element the closest to the parent element’s maximum size while maintaining aspect ratio.

english: Describes which axis to use when determining the new size of the element, while keeping respect to the aspect ratio.
translation: Describes which axis to use when determining the new size of the element, while keeping respect to the aspect ratio.

english: Uniformly scales a GUI object and all its children.
translation: Uniformly scales a GUI object and all its children.

english: The padding to apply on the left side relative to the parent's normal size.
translation: The padding to apply on the left side relative to the parent's normal size.

english: The padding to apply on the right side relative to the parent's normal size.
translation: The padding to apply on the right side relative to the parent's normal size.

english: The padding to apply on the top side relative to the parent's normal size.
translation: The padding to apply on the top side relative to the parent's normal size.

english: The padding to apply on the bottom side relative to the parent's normal size.
translation: The padding to apply on the bottom side relative to the parent's normal size.

english: The current state of how the tween is animating. Possible values are Begin, Playing, Paused, Completed and Cancelled. This property is modified by using functions such as Tween:Play(), Tween:Pause(), and Tween:Cancel(). Read-only.
translation: The current state of how the tween is animating. Possible values are Begin, Playing, Paused, Completed and Cancelled. This property is modified by using functions such as Tween:Play(), Tween:Pause(), and Tween:Cancel(). Read-only.

english: Starts or resumes (if Tween.PlaybackState is Paused) the tween animation. If current PlaybackState is Cancelled, this property will reset the tween to the beginning properties and play the animations from the beginning.
translation: Starts or resumes (if Tween.PlaybackState is Paused) the tween animation. If current PlaybackState is Cancelled, this property will reset the tween to the beginning properties and play the animations from the beginning.

english: Temporarily stops the tween animation. Animation can be resumed by calling Play().
translation: Temporarily stops the tween animation. Animation can be resumed by calling Play().

english: Stops the tween animation. Animation can be restarted by calling Play(). Animation will start from the beginning values.
translation: Stops the tween animation. Animation can be restarted by calling Play(). Animation will start from the beginning values.

english: Fires when the tween either reaches PlaybackState Completed or Cancelled. PlaybackState of one of these types is passed as the first arg to the function listening to this event.
translation: Fires when the tween either reaches PlaybackState Completed or Cancelled. PlaybackState of one of these types is passed as the first arg to the function listening to this event.

english: An object linked to an instance that animates properties on the instance over a specified period of time. Useful for easily moving UI objects around, rotating objects, etc. without having to write a lot of code. To create a new tween, please use TweenService:Create.
translation: An object linked to an instance that animates properties on the instance over a specified period of time. Useful for easily moving UI objects around, rotating objects, etc. without having to write a lot of code. To create a new tween, please use TweenService:Create.

english: The object this tween is operating on. Read-only.
translation: The object this tween is operating on. Read-only.

english: Specifies how the tween animates. Read-only.
translation: Specifies how the tween animates. Read-only.

english: Service responsible for creating tweens on instances.
translation: Service responsible for creating tweens on instances.

english: Creates a Tween object bound to a particular Instance. The first arg is the Instance to tween. The second arg is a TweenInfo struct, which specifies how a tween should behave. The third arg is a table, which should specify the properties to tween as keys, with the end value specified as values to the keys.
translation: Creates a Tween object bound to a particular Instance. The first arg is the Instance to tween. The second arg is a TweenInfo struct, which specifies how a tween should behave. The third arg is a table, which should specify the properties to tween as keys, with the end value specified as values to the keys.

english: Transforms a linear alpha to a given EasingStyle and EasingDirection.
translation: Transforms a linear alpha to a given EasingStyle and EasingDirection.

english: Will stop/begin certain core gui elements being rendered. See CoreGuiType for core guis that can be modified.
translation: Will stop/begin certain core gui elements being rendered. See CoreGuiType for core guis that can be modified.

english: Returns a boolean describing whether a CoreGuiType is currently being rendered.
translation: Returns a boolean describing whether a CoreGuiType is currently being rendered.

english: The GuiService is a special service, which currently allows developers to control what GuiObject is currently being selected by the Gamepad Gui navigator, and allows clients to check if Roblox's main menu is currently open. This service has a lot of hidden members, which are mainly used internally by Roblox's CoreScripts.
translation: The GuiService is a special service, which currently allows developers to control what GuiObject is currently being selected by the Gamepad Gui navigator, and allows clients to check if Roblox's main menu is currently open. This service has a lot of hidden members, which are mainly used internally by Roblox's CoreScripts.

english: Returns a Tuple containing two Vector2 values representing the offset of user GUIs in pixels from the top right corner of the screen and the bottom right corner of the screen respectively.
translation: Returns a Tuple containing two Vector2 values representing the offset of user GUIs in pixels from the top right corner of the screen and the bottom right corner of the screen respectively.

english: A service used to bind input to various lua functions.
translation: A service used to bind input to various lua functions.

english: Binds 'functionToBind' to fire when any 'inputTypes' happen. InputTypes can be variable in number and type. Types can be Enum.KeyCode, single character strings corresponding to keys, or Enum.UserInputType. 'actionName' is a key used by many other ContextActionService functions to query state. 'createTouchButton' if true will create a button on screen on touch devices.  This button will fire 'functionToBind' with three arguments: first argument is the actionName, second argument is the UserInputState of the input, and the third is the InputObject that fired this function. If 'functionToBind' yields or returns nil or Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input will be sunk. If it returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the next bound action in the stack will be invoked.
translation: Binds 'functionToBind' to fire when any 'inputTypes' happen. InputTypes can be variable in number and type. Types can be Enum.KeyCode, single character strings corresponding to keys, or Enum.UserInputType. 'actionName' is a key used by many other ContextActionService functions to query state. 'createTouchButton' if true will create a button on screen on touch devices.  This button will fire 'functionToBind' with three arguments: first argument is the actionName, second argument is the UserInputState of the input, and the third is the InputObject that fired this function. If 'functionToBind' yields or returns nil or Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input will be sunk. If it returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the next bound action in the stack will be invoked.

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'title' is set as the title of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether title will be set when button is manipulated.
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'title' is set as the title of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether title will be set when button is manipulated.

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'description' is set as the description of the bound action. This description will appear for users in a listing of current actions availables.
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'description' is set as the description of the bound action. This description will appear for users in a listing of current actions availables.

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'image' is set as the image of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether image will be set when button is manipulated.
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'image' is set as the image of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether image will be set when button is manipulated.

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'position' is set as the position of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether position will be set when button is manipulated.
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'position' is set as the position of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether position will be set when button is manipulated.

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, removes function from being called by all input that it was bound by (if function was also bound by a different action name as well, those bound input are still active). Will also remove any touch button created (if button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up).
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, removes function from being called by all input that it was bound by (if function was also bound by a different action name as well, those bound input are still active). Will also remove any touch button created (if button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up).

english: Removes all functions bound. No actionNames will remain. All touch buttons will be removed. If button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up.
translation: Removes all functions bound. No actionNames will remain. All touch buttons will be removed. If button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up.

english: Returns a table with info regarding the function bound with 'actionName'. Table has the keys 'title' (current title that was set with SetTitle) 'image' (image set with SetImage) 'description' (description set with SetDescription) 'inputTypes' (tuple containing all input bound for this 'actionName') 'createTouchButton' (whether or not we created a touch button for this 'actionName').
translation: Returns a table with info regarding the function bound with 'actionName'. Table has the keys 'title' (current title that was set with SetTitle) 'image' (image set with SetImage) 'description' (description set with SetDescription) 'inputTypes' (tuple containing all input bound for this 'actionName') 'createTouchButton' (whether or not we created a touch button for this 'actionName').

english: Returns a table with all bound action info. Each entry is a key with 'actionName' and value being the same table you would get from ContextActionService:GetBoundActionInfo('actionName').
translation: Returns a table with all bound action info. Each entry is a key with 'actionName' and value being the same table you would get from ContextActionService:GetBoundActionInfo('actionName').

english: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then this will return the touch button (if was created). Returns nil if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether button will be retrievable when button is manipulated.
translation: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then this will return the touch button (if was created). Returns nil if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether button will be retrievable when button is manipulated.

english: A service used to query and award points for Roblox users using the universal point system.
translation: A service used to query and award points for Roblox users using the universal point system.

english: Fired when points are successfully awarded 'userId'. Also returns the updated balance of points for usedId in universe via 'userBalanceInUniverse', total points via 'userTotalBalance', and the amount points that were awarded via 'pointsAwarded'. This event fires on the server and also all clients in the game that awarded the points.
translation: Fired when points are successfully awarded 'userId'. Also returns the updated balance of points for usedId in universe via 'userBalanceInUniverse', total points via 'userTotalBalance', and the amount points that were awarded via 'pointsAwarded'. This event fires on the server and also all clients in the game that awarded the points.

english: Will attempt to award the 'amount' points to 'userId', returns 'userId' awarded to, the number of points awarded, the new point total the user has in the game, and the total number of points the user now has. Will also fire PointsService.PointsAwarded. Works with server scripts ONLY.
translation: Will attempt to award the 'amount' points to 'userId', returns 'userId' awarded to, the number of points awarded, the new point total the user has in the game, and the total number of points the user now has. Will also fire PointsService.PointsAwarded. Works with server scripts ONLY.

english: Returns the overall balance of points that player with userId has (the sum of all points across all games). Works with server scripts ONLY.
translation: Returns the overall balance of points that player with userId has (the sum of all points across all games). Works with server scripts ONLY.

english: Returns the balance of points that player with userId has in the current game (all placeID points combined within the game). Works with server scripts ONLY.
translation: Returns the balance of points that player with userId has in the current game (all placeID points combined within the game). Works with server scripts ONLY.

english: Returns the number of points the current universe can award to players. Works with server scripts ONLY.
translation: Returns the number of points the current universe can award to players. Works with server scripts ONLY.

english: A database of strings used in the game and their translations.
translation: A database of strings used in the game and their translations.

english: Gets the system's preferred language (A Language enum).
translation: Gets the system's preferred language (A Language enum).

english: Will prompt 'player' to purchase the item associated with 'assetId'.  'equipIfPurchased' is an optional argument that will give the item to the player immediately if they buy it (only applies to gear).  'currencyType' is also optional and will attempt to prompt the user with a specified currency if the product can be purchased with this currency, otherwise we use the default currency of the product.
translation: Will prompt 'player' to purchase the item associated with 'assetId'.  'equipIfPurchased' is an optional argument that will give the item to the player immediately if they buy it (only applies to gear).  'currencyType' is also optional and will attempt to prompt the user with a specified currency if the product can be purchased with this currency, otherwise we use the default currency of the product.

english: Takes one argument \"assetId\" which should be a number of an asset on www.roblox.com.  Returns a table containing the product information (if this process fails, returns an empty table).
translation: Takes one argument \"assetId\" which should be a number of an asset on www.roblox.com.  Returns a table containing the product information (if this process fails, returns an empty table).

english: Checks to see if 'Player' owns the product associated with 'assetId'. Returns true if the player owns it, false otherwise. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.
translation: Checks to see if 'Player' owns the product associated with 'assetId'. Returns true if the player owns it, false otherwise. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.

english:
Callback that is executed for pending Developer Product receipts.

If this function does not return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted, then you will not be granted the money for the purchase!

The callback will be invoked with a table, containing the following informational fields:

  • PlayerId: int64 - the id of the player making the purchase.
  • PlaceIdWherePurchased: int64: - the specific place where the purchase was made.
  • PurchaseId: string - a unique identifier for the purchase, should be used to prevent granting an item multiple times for one purchase.
  • ProductId: int64 - the id of the purchased product.
  • CurrencyType: CurrencyType - the type of currency used (Tix, Robux).
  • CurrencySpent: int - the amount of currency spent on the product for this purchase.
translation:
Callback that is executed for pending Developer Product receipts.

If this function does not return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted, then you will not be granted the money for the purchase!

The callback will be invoked with a table, containing the following informational fields:

  • PlayerId: int64 - the id of the player making the purchase.
  • PlaceIdWherePurchased: int64: - the specific place where the purchase was made.
  • PurchaseId: string - a unique identifier for the purchase, should be used to prevent granting an item multiple times for one purchase.
  • ProductId: int64 - the id of the purchased product.
  • CurrencyType: CurrencyType - the type of currency used (Tix, Robux).
  • CurrencySpent: int - the amount of currency spent on the product for this purchase.

english: Fired when a 'player' dismisses a purchase dialog for 'assetId'.  If the player purchased the item 'isPurchased' will be true, otherwise it will be false. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.
translation: Fired when a 'player' dismisses a purchase dialog for 'assetId'.  If the player purchased the item 'isPurchased' will be true, otherwise it will be false. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.

english: Returns true if the local device accepts touch input, false otherwise.
translation: Returns true if the local device accepts touch input, false otherwise.

english: Returns true if the local device accepts keyboard input, false otherwise.
translation: Returns true if the local device accepts keyboard input, false otherwise.

english: Returns true if the local device accepts mouse input, false otherwise.
translation: Returns true if the local device accepts mouse input, false otherwise.

english: Returns true if the local device has an accelerometer, false otherwise.
translation: Returns true if the local device has an accelerometer, false otherwise.

english: Returns true if the local device has an gyroscope, false otherwise.
translation: Returns true if the local device has an gyroscope, false otherwise.

english: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user places their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user places their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user clicks/taps on a textbox to begin text entry. Argument is the textbox that was put in focus. This also fires if a textbox forces focus on the user. This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user clicks/taps on a textbox to begin text entry. Argument is the textbox that was put in focus. This also fires if a textbox forces focus on the user. This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user stops text entry into a textbox (usually by pressing return or clicking/tapping somewhere else on the screen). Argument is the textbox that was taken out of focus. This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user stops text entry into a textbox (usually by pressing return or clicking/tapping somewhere else on the screen). Argument is the textbox that was taken out of focus. This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user moves a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user moves a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when the force of gravity changes on a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when the force of gravity changes on a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user rotates a device that has an gyroscope. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. A second argument of Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user rotates a device that has an gyroscope. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. A second argument of Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.

english: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current acceleration. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.
translation: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current acceleration. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.

english: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current gravity vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.
translation: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current gravity vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.

english: Returns an InputObject and a Vector4 that describes the device's current rotation vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. The Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.
translation: Returns an InputObject and a Vector4 that describes the device's current rotation vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. The Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.

english: Attempts to move the Humanoid and it's associated character to 'part'. 'location' is used as an offset from part's origin.
translation: Attempts to move the Humanoid and it's associated character to 'part'. 'location' is used as an offset from part's origin.

english: Decreases health by the amount.  Use this instead of changing health directly to make sure weapons are filtered for things such as ForceField(s).
translation: Decreases health by the amount.  Use this instead of changing health directly to make sure weapons are filtered for things such as ForceField(s).

english: Takes any active gear/tools that the Humanoid is using and puts them into the backpack.  This function only works on Humanoids with a corresponding Player.
translation: Takes any active gear/tools that the Humanoid is using and puts them into the backpack.  This function only works on Humanoids with a corresponding Player.

english: Takes a specified tool and equips it to the Humanoid's Character.  Tool argument should be of type 'Tool'.
translation: Takes a specified tool and equips it to the Humanoid's Character.  Tool argument should be of type 'Tool'.

english: Replaces the desired bodypart on the Humanoid's Character using a specified Enum.BodyPartR15 and BasePart. Returns a success boolean.
translation: Replaces the desired bodypart on the Humanoid's Character using a specified Enum.BodyPartR15 and BasePart. Returns a success boolean.

english: Returns a Enum.BodyPartR15 given a body part in the Humanoid's Character.
translation: Returns a Enum.BodyPartR15 given a body part in the Humanoid's Character.

english: Sets how to display other humanoid names to this humanoid's player. More info
translation: Sets how to display other humanoid names to this humanoid's player. More info

english: How many hit points the Humanoid has.  When this number reaches 0 or goes below 0, the Humanoid's character falls apart and will respawn.
translation: How many hit points the Humanoid has.  When this number reaches 0 or goes below 0, the Humanoid's character falls apart and will respawn.

english: The maximum number of hit points a Humanoid's health can reach.  If the Humanoid's health is set over this amount, the health gets set to this value.
translation: The maximum number of hit points a Humanoid's health can reach.  If the Humanoid's health is set over this amount, the health gets set to this value.

english: The location that the Humanoid is trying to walk to.
translation: The location that the Humanoid is trying to walk to.

english: Humanoid.RootPart will be the preferred way of getting a character's humanoid root part.
translation: Humanoid.RootPart will be the preferred way of getting a character's humanoid root part.

english: In R6 this property get the player's left leg. In R15 this gets nothing.
translation: In R6 this property get the player's left leg. In R15 this gets nothing.

english: In R6 this property get the player's right leg. In R15 this gets nothing.
translation: In R6 this property get the player's right leg. In R15 this gets nothing.

english: An emum that selects the collision type for R15 and Rthro characters. InnerBox is classic style collisions for all characters, OuterBox is dynamically sized collisions based on Mesh size.
translation: An emum that selects the collision type for R15 and Rthro characters. InnerBox is classic style collisions for all characters, OuterBox is dynamically sized collisions based on Mesh size.

english: Determines whether or not an Instance can be saved when the game closes/attempts to save the game. Note: this only applies to games that use Data Persistence, or SavePlaceAsync.
translation: Determines whether or not an Instance can be saved when the game closes/attempts to save the game. Note: this only applies to games that use Data Persistence, or SavePlaceAsync.

english: The string name of this Instance's most derived class.
translation: The string name of this Instance's most derived class.

english: The Instance that is directly above this Instance in the tree.
translation: The Instance that is directly above this Instance in the tree.

english: This function is for internal testing. Don't use in production code
translation: This function is for internal testing. Don't use in production code

english: Returns a boolean if this Instance is of type 'className' or a is a subclass of type 'className'. If 'className' is not a valid class type in ROBLOX, this function will always return false. More info
translation: Returns a boolean if this Instance is of type 'className' or a is a subclass of type 'className'. If 'className' is not a valid class type in ROBLOX, this function will always return false. More info

english: Returns the first child of this Instance that with a ClassName equal to 'className'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.
translation: Returns the first child of this Instance that with a ClassName equal to 'className'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.

english: Returns the first child of this Instance that :IsA(className).  The second argument 'recursive' is an optional boolean (defaults to false) that will force the call to traverse down thru all of this Instance's descendants until it finds an object with a name that matches the 'className' argument.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.
translation: Returns the first child of this Instance that :IsA(className).  The second argument 'recursive' is an optional boolean (defaults to false) that will force the call to traverse down thru all of this Instance's descendants until it finds an object with a name that matches the 'className' argument.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.

english: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance that matches the first argument 'name'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.
translation: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance that matches the first argument 'name'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.

english: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance with a ClassName equal to 'className'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.
translation: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance with a ClassName equal to 'className'.  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.

english: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance that :IsA(className).  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.
translation: Returns the first ancestor of this Instance that :IsA(className).  The function will return nil if no Instance is found.

english: Returns a string that shows the path from the root node (DataModel) to this Instance.  This string does not include the root node (DataModel).
translation: Returns a string that shows the path from the root node (DataModel) to this Instance.  This string does not include the root node (DataModel).

english: Returns a read-only table of this Object's children
translation: Returns a read-only table of this Object's children

english: Returns an array containing all of the descendants of the instance. Returns in preorder traversal, or in other words, where the parents come before their children, depth first.
translation: Returns an array containing all of the descendants of the instance. Returns in preorder traversal, or in other words, where the parents come before their children, depth first.

english: Removes all children (but not this object) from the workspace.
translation: Removes all children (but not this object) from the workspace.

english: Removes object and all of its children from the workspace. Disconnects object and all children from open connections. Object and children may not be usable after calling Destroy.
translation: Removes object and all of its children from the workspace. Disconnects object and all children from open connections. Object and children may not be usable after calling Destroy.

english: Fired when any of this object's ancestors change.  First argument 'child' is the object whose parent changed.  Second argument 'parent' is the first argument's new parent.
translation: Fired when any of this object's ancestors change.  First argument 'child' is the object whose parent changed.  Second argument 'parent' is the first argument's new parent.

english: Fired after an Instance is parented to this object, or any of this object's descendants.  The 'descendant' argument is the Instance that is being added.
translation: Fired after an Instance is parented to this object, or any of this object's descendants.  The 'descendant' argument is the Instance that is being added.

english: Fired after an Instance is unparented from this object, or any of this object's descendants.  The 'descendant' argument is the Instance that is being added.
translation: Fired after an Instance is unparented from this object, or any of this object's descendants.  The 'descendant' argument is the Instance that is being added.

english: Fired after a property changes value.  The property argument is the name of the property
translation: Fired after a property changes value.  The property argument is the name of the property

english: Attempts to maintain a fixed orientation of its parent Part
translation: Attempts to maintain a fixed orientation of its parent Part

english: The dampening factor applied to this force
translation: The dampening factor applied to this force

english: The power continually applied to this force
translation: The power continually applied to this force

english: The dampening factor applied to this force
translation: The dampening factor applied to this force

english: The power factor continually applied to this force
translation: The power factor continually applied to this force

english: A propulsion system that mimics a rocket
translation: A propulsion system that mimics a rocket

english: The amount of power we add to the system.  The higher the power, the quicker the force will achieve its goal.
translation: The amount of power we add to the system.  The higher the power, the quicker the force will achieve its goal.

english: When parented to a physical part, BodyForce will continually exert a force upon its parent object.
translation: When parented to a physical part, BodyForce will continually exert a force upon its parent object.

english: This Service-level object is the container for all Team objects in a level. A map that supports team games must have a Teams service. More info
translation: This Service-level object is the container for all Team objects in a level. A map that supports team games must have a Teams service. More info

english: Returns a read-only table of players which are on this team.
translation: Returns a read-only table of players which are on this team.

english: The Team class is used to represent a faction in a team game. The only valid location for a Team object is under the Teams service. More info
translation: The Team class is used to represent a faction in a team game. The only valid location for a Team object is under the Teams service. More info

english: The name of the player who is currently editing the script in Team Create.
translation: The name of the player who is currently editing the script in Team Create.

english: This property is under development. Do not use
translation: This property is under development. Do not use

english: A script that runs on clients, NOT servers.  LocalScripts can only run when parented under one of the following:1) A player's Backpack.2) A player's Character model.3) A player's PlayerGui.4) A player's PlayerScripts.5) The ReplicatedFirst service.
translation: A script that runs on clients, NOT servers.  LocalScripts can only run when parented under one of the following:1) A player's Backpack.2) A player's Character model.3) A player's PlayerGui.4) A player's PlayerScripts.5) The ReplicatedFirst service.

english: A construct used to group Parts and other objects together, also allows manipulation of multiple objects.
translation: A construct used to group Parts and other objects together, also allows manipulation of multiple objects.

english: Breaks all surface joints contained within
translation: Breaks all surface joints contained within

english: Returns a CFrame that has position of the centroid of all Parts in the Model.  The rotation matrix is either the rotation matrix of the user-defined PrimaryPart, or if not specified then  a part in the Model chosen by the engine.
translation: Returns a CFrame that has position of the centroid of all Parts in the Model.  The rotation matrix is either the rotation matrix of the user-defined PrimaryPart, or if not specified then  a part in the Model chosen by the engine.

english: Returns a Vector3 that is union of the extents of all Parts in the model.
translation: Returns a Vector3 that is union of the extents of all Parts in the model.

english: Moves the centroid of the Model to the specified location, respecting all relative distances between parts in the model.
translation: Moves the centroid of the Model to the specified location, respecting all relative distances between parts in the model.

english: Rotates all parts in the model to the orientation that was set using SetIdentityOrientation().  If this function has never been called, rotation is reset to GetModelCFrame()'s rotation.
translation: Rotates all parts in the model to the orientation that was set using SetIdentityOrientation().  If this function has never been called, rotation is reset to GetModelCFrame()'s rotation.

english: Takes the current rotation matrix of the model and stores it as the model's identity matrix. The rotation is applied when ResetOrientationToIdentity() is called.
translation: Takes the current rotation matrix of the model and stores it as the model's identity matrix. The rotation is applied when ResetOrientationToIdentity() is called.

english: Similar to MoveTo(), except instead of moving to an explicit location, we use the model's current CFrame location and offset it.
translation: Similar to MoveTo(), except instead of moving to an explicit location, we use the model's current CFrame location and offset it.

english: Returns the cframe of the Model.PrimaryPart. If PrimaryPart is nil, then this function will throw an error.
translation: Returns the cframe of the Model.PrimaryPart. If PrimaryPart is nil, then this function will throw an error.

english: Sets the cframe of the Model.PrimaryPart. If PrimaryPart is nil, then this function will throw an error. This also sets the cframe of all descendant Parts relative to the cframe change to PrimaryPart.
translation: Sets the cframe of the Model.PrimaryPart. If PrimaryPart is nil, then this function will throw an error. This also sets the cframe of all descendant Parts relative to the cframe change to PrimaryPart.

english: A Part that serves as a reference for the Model's CFrame. Used in conjunction with GetModelPrimaryPartCFrame and SetModelPrimaryPartCFrame. Use this to rotate/translate all Parts relative to the PrimaryPart.
translation: A Part that serves as a reference for the Model's CFrame. Used in conjunction with GetModelPrimaryPartCFrame and SetModelPrimaryPartCFrame. Use this to rotate/translate all Parts relative to the PrimaryPart.

english: The root of ROBLOX's parent-child hierarchy (commonly known as game after the global variable used to access it)
translation: The root of ROBLOX's parent-child hierarchy (commonly known as game after the global variable used to access it)
