english: Returns true if the game has finished loading, false otherwise.  Check this before listening to the Loaded signal to ensure a script knows when a game finishes loading.
translation: Returns true if the game has finished loading, false otherwise.  Check this before listening to the Loaded signal to ensure a script knows when a game finishes loading.

english: Fires when the game finishes loading.  Use this to know when to remove your custom loading gui.  It is best to check IsLoaded() before connecting to this event, as the game may load before the event is connected to.
translation: Fires when the game finishes loading.  Use this to know when to remove your custom loading gui.  It is best to check IsLoaded() before connecting to this event, as the game may load before the event is connected to.

english: Responsible for storing data across multiple user created places
translation: Responsible for storing data across multiple user created places

english: Returns a data store with the given name and scope
translation: Returns a data store with the given name and scope

english: Returns an ordered data store with the given name and scope
translation: Returns an ordered data store with the given name and scope

english: Exposes functions for saving and loading data for the DataStoreService
translation: Exposes functions for saving and loading data for the DataStoreService

english: Sets callback as a function to be executed any time the value associated with key is changed. It is important to disconnect the connection when the subscription to the key is no longer needed.
translation: Sets callback as a function to be executed any time the value associated with key is changed. It is important to disconnect the connection when the subscription to the key is no longer needed.

english: Returns the value of the entry in the DataStore with the given key
translation: Returns the value of the entry in the DataStore with the given key

english: Increments the value of a particular key amd returns the incremented value
translation: Increments the value of a particular key amd returns the incremented value

english: Sets the value of the key. This overwrites any existing data stored in the key
translation: Sets the value of the key. This overwrites any existing data stored in the key

english: Retrieves the value of the key from the website, and updates it with a new value. The callback until the value fetched matches the value on the web. Returning nil means it will not save.
translation: Retrieves the value of the key from the website, and updates it with a new value. The callback until the value fetched matches the value on the web. Returning nil means it will not save.

english: A type of DataStore where values must be positive integers. This makes OrderedDataStore suitable for leaderboard related scripting where you are required to order large amounts of data efficiently.
translation: A type of DataStore where values must be positive integers. This makes OrderedDataStore suitable for leaderboard related scripting where you are required to order large amounts of data efficiently.

english: Returns a DataStorePages object. The length of each page is determined by pageSize, and the order is determined by isAscending. minValue and maxValue are optional parameters which will filter the result.
translation: Returns a DataStorePages object. The length of each page is determined by pageSize, and the order is determined by isAscending. minValue and maxValue are optional parameters which will filter the result.

english: Where the Camera's focus is.  Any rotation of the camera will be about this subject.
translation: Where the Camera's focus is.  Any rotation of the camera will be about this subject.

english: Defines how the camera will behave. More info
translation: Defines how the camera will behave. More info

english: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
translation: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.

english: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
translation: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.

english: The current angle, or width, of what the camera can see.  Current acceptable values are from 20 degrees to 80.
translation: The current angle, or width, of what the camera can see.  Current acceptable values are from 20 degrees to 80.

english: The current CoordinateFrame that the camera is looking at.  Note: it is not always guaranteed that the camera is always looking here.
translation: The current CoordinateFrame that the camera is looking at.  Note: it is not always guaranteed that the camera is always looking here.

english: Holds the x,y screen resolution of the viewport the camera is presenting (note: this can differ from the AbsoluteSize property of a full screen gui).
translation: Holds the x,y screen resolution of the viewport the camera is presenting (note: this can differ from the AbsoluteSize property of a full screen gui).

english: The negative z-offset of the view frustum's near clipping plane.
translation: The negative z-offset of the view frustum's near clipping plane.

english: Returns the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
translation: Returns the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.

english: Takes a 3D position in the world and projects it onto x,y coordinates of screen space. Returns two values, first is a Vector3 that has x,y position and z position which is distance from camera (negative if behind camera, positive if in front). Second return value is a boolean indicating if the first argument is an on-screen coordinate.
translation: Takes a 3D position in the world and projects it onto x,y coordinates of screen space. Returns two values, first is a Vector3 that has x,y position and z position which is distance from camera (negative if behind camera, positive if in front). Second return value is a boolean indicating if the first argument is an on-screen coordinate.

english: Takes a 2D screen position and produces a Ray object to be used for 3D raycasting. Input is x,y screen coordinates, and a (optional, defaults to 0) z position which sets how far in the camera look vector to start the ray origin.
translation: Takes a 2D screen position and produces a Ray object to be used for 3D raycasting. Input is x,y screen coordinates, and a (optional, defaults to 0) z position which sets how far in the camera look vector to start the ray origin.

english: Same as ScreenPointToRay, except no GUI offsets are taken into account. Useful for things like casting a ray from the middle of the Camera.ViewportSize
translation: Same as ScreenPointToRay, except no GUI offsets are taken into account. Useful for things like casting a ray from the middle of the Camera.ViewportSize

english: Same as WorldToScreenPoint, except no GUI offsets are taken into account.
translation: Same as WorldToScreenPoint, except no GUI offsets are taken into account.

english: Sets the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
translation: Sets the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.

english: Set to true, when a player joins a game, they get a character automatically, as well as when they die.  When set to false, characters do not auto load and will only load in using Player:LoadCharacter().
translation: Set to true, when a player joins a game, they get a character automatically, as well as when they die.  When set to false, characters do not auto load and will only load in using Player:LoadCharacter().

english: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients and the server.
translation: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients and the server.

english: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients (but not back to the server) first before anything else. Useful for creating loading guis, tutorials, etc.
translation: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients (but not back to the server) first before anything else. Useful for creating loading guis, tutorials, etc.

english: Removes the default Roblox loading screen from view. Call this when you are ready to either show your own loading gui, or when the game is ready to play.
translation: Removes the default Roblox loading screen from view. Call this when you are ready to either show your own loading gui, or when the game is ready to play.

english: A container whose contents are only on the server.
translation: A container whose contents are only on the server.

english: A container whose contents should be scripts. Scripts that are added to the container are run on the server.
translation: A container whose contents should be scripts. Scripts that are added to the container are run on the server.

english: A service for interfacing with the current studio state from Lua.
translation: A service for interfacing with the current studio state from Lua.

english: Responsible for all lighting aspects of the world (affects how things are rendered).
translation: Responsible for all lighting aspects of the world (affects how things are rendered).

english: The number of minutes that the current time is past midnight.  If currently at midnight, returns 0.  Will return decimal values if not at an exact minute.
translation: The number of minutes that the current time is past midnight.  If currently at midnight, returns 0.  Will return decimal values if not at an exact minute.

english: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the moon. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the moon.
translation: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the moon. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the moon.

english: Currently always returns 0.75. MoonPhase cannot be edited.
translation: Currently always returns 0.75. MoonPhase cannot be edited.

english: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the sun. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the sun.
translation: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the sun. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the sun.

english: Sets the time to be a certain number of minutes after midnight.  This works with integer and decimal values.
translation: Sets the time to be a certain number of minutes after midnight.  This works with integer and decimal values.

english: The hue of the global lighting.  Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the Workspace.
translation: The hue of the global lighting.  Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the Workspace.

english: How much global light each Part in the Workspace receives. Standard range is 0 to 2 (0 being little light), but can be increased all the way to 10 (colors start to be appear very different at this value).
translation: How much global light each Part in the Workspace receives. Standard range is 0 to 2 (0 being little light), but can be increased all the way to 10 (colors start to be appear very different at this value).

english: Exposure compensation amount. Applies a bias to the exposure level prior to the tonemap step. +1 indicates twice as much exposure and -1 means half as much exposure.
translation: Exposure compensation amount. Applies a bias to the exposure level prior to the tonemap step. +1 indicates twice as much exposure and -1 means half as much exposure.

english: This property controls how blurry the shadows are.
translation: This property controls how blurry the shadows are.

english: The hue of global lighting on the bottom surfaces of an object.
translation: The hue of global lighting on the bottom surfaces of an object.

english: The hue of global lighting on the top surfaces of an object.
translation: The hue of global lighting on the top surfaces of an object.

english: A Color3 value that changes the hue of distance fog.
translation: A Color3 value that changes the hue of distance fog.

english: The distance at which fog completely blocks your vision. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs
translation: The distance at which fog completely blocks your vision. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs

english: The distance at which the fog gradient begins. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs.
translation: The distance at which the fog gradient begins. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs.

english: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. More info
translation: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. More info

english: Flag enabling shadows from sun and moon in the place
translation: Flag enabling shadows from sun and moon in the place

english: Effective ambient value for outdoors, effectively shadow color outdoors (requires GlobalShadows enabled)
translation: Effective ambient value for outdoors, effectively shadow color outdoors (requires GlobalShadows enabled)

english: Flag enabling or disabling outlines on parts and terrain
translation: Flag enabling or disabling outlines on parts and terrain

english: Color the shadows appear as. Shadows are drawn mostly for characters, but depending on the lighting will also show for Parts in the Workspace.  Rendering settings can also affect if shadows are drawn.
translation: Color the shadows appear as. Shadows are drawn mostly for characters, but depending on the lighting will also show for Parts in the Workspace.  Rendering settings can also affect if shadows are drawn.

english: A string that represent the current time of day. Time is in 24-hour clock format \"XX::YY:ZZ\", where X is hour, Y is minute, and Z is seconds.
translation: A string that represent the current time of day. Time is in 24-hour clock format \"XX::YY:ZZ\", where X is hour, Y is minute, and Z is seconds.

english: Fired whenever a property of Lighting is changed, or a skybox is added or removed. Skyboxes are of type 'Sky' and should be parented directly to lighting.
translation: Fired whenever a property of Lighting is changed, or a skybox is added or removed. Skyboxes are of type 'Sky' and should be parented directly to lighting.

english: A service that provides utility in cleaning up objects
translation: A service that provides utility in cleaning up objects

english: Adds an Instance into the debris service that will later be destroyed.  Second argument 'lifetime' is optional and specifies how long (in seconds) to wait before destroying the item. If no time is specified then the item added will automatically be destroyed in 10 seconds.
translation: Adds an Instance into the debris service that will later be destroyed.  Second argument 'lifetime' is optional and specifies how long (in seconds) to wait before destroying the item. If no time is specified then the item added will automatically be destroyed in 10 seconds.

english: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. More info.
translation: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. More info.

english: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. Info on Data Persistence.
translation: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. Info on Data Persistence.

english: Loads in a new character for this player.  This will replace the player's current character, if they have one. This should be used in conjunction with Players.CharacterAutoLoads to control spawning of characters. This function only works from a server-side script (NOT a LocalScript).
translation: Loads in a new character for this player.  This will replace the player's current character, if they have one. This should be used in conjunction with Players.CharacterAutoLoads to control spawning of characters. This function only works from a server-side script (NOT a LocalScript).

english: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. Info on Data Persistence.
translation: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. Info on Data Persistence.

english: Fired periodically after the user has been AFK for a while.  Currently this event is only fired for the *local* Player.  \"time\" is the time in seconds that the user has been idle.
translation: Fired periodically after the user has been AFK for a while.  Currently this event is only fired for the *local* Player.  \"time\" is the time in seconds that the user has been idle.

english: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
translation: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less

english: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
translation: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less

english: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
translation: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

english: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
translation: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

english: Boolean used to enable the new physics solver
translation: Boolean used to enable the new physics solver

english: Sets the height at which falling characters and parts are destroyed. This property is not scriptable and can only be set in Studio
translation: Sets the height at which falling characters and parts are destroyed. This property is not scriptable and can only be set in Studio

english: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. More info
translation: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. More info

english: Determines whether physical interactions with other Parts are respected.  If true, will collide and react with physics to other Parts.  If false, other parts will pass thru instead of colliding
translation: Determines whether physical interactions with other Parts are respected.  If true, will collide and react with physics to other Parts.  If false, other parts will pass thru instead of colliding

english: Determines whether or not physics acts upon the Part.  If true, part stays 'Anchored' in space, not moving regardless of any collision/forces acting upon it.  If false, physics works normally on the part.
translation: Determines whether or not physics acts upon the Part.  If true, part stays 'Anchored' in space, not moving regardless of any collision/forces acting upon it.  If false, physics works normally on the part.

english: If true the part will be massless when welded to another part that is not massless. The part will still have mass like a normal part if it is an assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
translation: If true the part will be massless when welded to another part that is not massless. The part will still have mass like a normal part if it is an assembly root part according to GetRootPart().

english: An integer from -127 to 127. Compares before other all other part properties besides massless for deciding which part is the assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
translation: An integer from -127 to 127. Compares before other all other part properties besides massless for deciding which part is the assembly root part according to GetRootPart().

english: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will rebound against another. a value of 1 is like a superball, and 0 is like a lead block.
translation: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will rebound against another. a value of 1 is like a superball, and 0 is like a lead block.

english: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will be able to slide. a value of 1 is no sliding, and 0 is no friction, so infinite sliding.
translation: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will be able to slide. a value of 1 is no sliding, and 0 is no friction, so infinite sliding.

english: Determines whether building tools (in-game and studio) can manipulate this Part.  If true, no editing allowed.  If false, editing is allowed.
translation: Determines whether building tools (in-game and studio) can manipulate this Part.  If true, no editing allowed.  If false, editing is allowed.

english: Determines whether this Part casts a shadow.
translation: Determines whether this Part casts a shadow.

english: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. More info
translation: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. More info

english: Specifies how shiny the Part is. A value of 1 is completely reflective (chrome), while a value of 0 is no reflectance (concrete wall)
translation: Specifies how shiny the Part is. A value of 1 is completely reflective (chrome), while a value of 0 is no reflectance (concrete wall)

english: Sets the value for the smallest change in size allowable by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
translation: Sets the value for the smallest change in size allowable by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.

english: Sets the value for the faces allowed to be resized by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
translation: Sets the value for the faces allowed to be resized by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.

english: Sets how visible an object is. A value of 1 makes the object invisible, while a value of 0 makes the object opaque.
translation: Sets how visible an object is. A value of 1 makes the object invisible, while a value of 0 makes the object opaque.

english: How fast the Part is traveling in studs/second. This property is NOT recommended to be modified directly, unless there is good reason.  Otherwise, try using a BodyForce to move a Part.
translation: How fast the Part is traveling in studs/second. This property is NOT recommended to be modified directly, unless there is good reason.  Otherwise, try using a BodyForce to move a Part.

english: Position relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
translation: Position relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.

english: Orientation relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
translation: Orientation relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.

english: Rotation around X, Y, and Z axis.  Rotations applied in YXZ order.
translation: Rotation around X, Y, and Z axis.  Rotations applied in YXZ order.

english: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. More info
translation: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. More info

english: Destroys SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model).
translation: Destroys SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model).

english: Resizes a Part in the direction of the face defined by 'NormalId', by the amount specified by 'deltaAmount'. If the operation will expand the part to intersect another Instance, the part will not resize at all.  Return true if the call is successful, false otherwise.
translation: Resizes a Part in the direction of the face defined by 'NormalId', by the amount specified by 'deltaAmount'. If the operation will expand the part to intersect another Instance, the part will not resize at all.  Return true if the call is successful, false otherwise.

english: Fired when the part stops touching another part
translation: Fired when the part stops touching another part

english: A plastic building block - the fundamental component of ROBLOX
translation: A plastic building block - the fundamental component of ROBLOX

english: A container instance that syncs data between a single player and the server.  ScreenGui objects that are placed in this container will be shown to the Player parent only
translation: A container instance that syncs data between a single player and the server.  ScreenGui objects that are placed in this container will be shown to the Player parent only

english: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
translation: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.

english: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be exectue only when a Player is the parent.
translation: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be exectue only when a Player is the parent.

english: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new Players on startup.
translation: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new Players on startup.

english: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new characters on startup.
translation: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new characters on startup.

english: The base class of ScreenGui, BillboardGui, and SurfaceGui.
translation: The base class of ScreenGui, BillboardGui, and SurfaceGui.

english: The core GUI object on which tools are built.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered as a 2D overlay
translation: The core GUI object on which tools are built.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered as a 2D overlay

english: A GUI that adorns an object in the 3D world.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered while attached to a 3D object
translation: A GUI that adorns an object in the 3D world.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered while attached to a 3D object

english: The Object the billboard gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
translation: The Object the billboard gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.

english: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
translation: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

english: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
translation: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

english: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
translation: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

english: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.
translation: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.

english: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
translation: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

english: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.
translation: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.

english: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.
translation: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.

english: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from
translation: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from

english: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.
translation: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.

english: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.
translation: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.

english: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
translation: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

english: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.
translation: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.

english: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
translation: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.

english: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
translation: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

english: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
translation: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

english: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
translation: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

english: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
translation: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

english: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
translation: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

english: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.
translation: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.

english: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.
translation: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.

english: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.
translation: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.

english: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.
translation: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.

english: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.
translation: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.

english: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info
translation: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info

english: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info
translation: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info

english: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info
translation: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info

english: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
translation: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

english: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
translation: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

english: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
translation: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

english: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
translation: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

english: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
translation: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

english: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.
translation: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.

english: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.
translation: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.

english: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.
translation: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.

english: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.
translation: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.

english: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.
translation: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.

english: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).
translation: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).

english: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
translation: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.

english: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.
translation: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.

english: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.
translation: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.

english: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
translation: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

english: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
translation: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

english: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
translation: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

english: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
translation: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

english: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.
translation: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.

english: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

english: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
translation: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

english: A container object used to layout other GUI objects
translation: A container object used to layout other GUI objects

english: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info
translation: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info

english: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.
translation: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.

english: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.
translation: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.

english: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.
translation: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.

english: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.
translation: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.

english: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.
translation: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.

english: The \"Up\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the \"left\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
translation: The \"Up\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the \"left\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

english: The \"Middle\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the \"mid\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
translation: The \"Middle\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the \"mid\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

english: The \"Down\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the \"right\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
translation: The \"Down\" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the \"right\" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

english: A GUI object containing an Image
translation: A GUI object containing an Image

english: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info
translation: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info

english: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.
translation: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

english: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.
translation: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.

english: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.
translation: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.

english: A GUI button containing an Image
translation: A GUI button containing an Image

english: Determines whether a button changes color automatically when reacting to mouse events.
translation: Determines whether a button changes color automatically when reacting to mouse events.

english: Allows the mouse to be free in first person mode. If a button with this property set to true is visible, the mouse is 'free' in first person mode.
translation: Allows the mouse to be free in first person mode. If a button with this property set to true is visible, the mouse is 'free' in first person mode.

english: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. More info
translation: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. More info

english: Fired when the mouse is over the button, and the mouse down and up events fire without the mouse leaving the button.
translation: Fired when the mouse is over the button, and the mouse down and up events fire without the mouse leaving the button.

english: Fired when the mouse button is pushed down on a button.
translation: Fired when the mouse button is pushed down on a button.

english: Fired when the mouse button is released on a button.
translation: Fired when the mouse button is released on a button.

translation: A GUI that can show 3D objects

translation: A number value that specifies how transparent the rendered image of the ViewportFrame is

english: The rendered image of the ViewportFrame will be mutiplied by this color
translation: The rendered image of the ViewportFrame will be mutiplied by this color

english: Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the ViewportFrame.
translation: Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the ViewportFrame.

english: Directional light color for objects in the ViewportFrame.
translation: Directional light color for objects in the ViewportFrame.

english: Light direction. Value will be normalized. All values valid except (0,0,0).
translation: Light direction. Value will be normalized. All values valid except (0,0,0).

translation: A GUI button containing an Image

english: Specifies the asset id of the texture to display. More info

english: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.
translation: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

english: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.

english: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable handles
translation: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable handles

english: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable arc handles
translation: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable arc handles

english: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object
translation: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object

english: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object
translation: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object

translation: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around a face of an object

translation: An object that can be placed under parts to hold Value objects that represent that part's configuration

english: An object that specifies the appearance of Humanoid characters
translation: An object that specifies the appearance of Humanoid characters

english: An object that can be created to hold and organize objects
translation: An object that can be created to hold and organize objects

english: A visual line drawn representation between two part objects
translation: A visual line drawn representation between two part objects

english: A visual line drawn representation between two positions
translation: A visual line drawn representation between two positions

english: A visual line drawn representation between two parts.
translation: A visual line drawn representation between two parts.

translation: The pose of a joint relative to it's parent part in a keyframe

english: Represents when an event should be fired in an animation
translation: Represents when an event should be fired in an animation

english: Represents a linked animation object, containing keyframes and poses.
translation: Represents a linked animation object, containing keyframes and poses.

english: Returned by a call to LoadAnimation. Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid.
translation: Returned by a call to LoadAnimation. Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid.

english: Allows animations to be played on joints of the parent object.
translation: Allows animations to be played on joints of the parent object.

english: Modifies the appearance of a body part.
translation: Modifies the appearance of a body part.

english: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players
translation: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players

english: The maximum distance that the player's character can be from the dialog's parent in order to use the dialog.
translation: The maximum distance that the player's character can be from the dialog's parent in order to use the dialog.

english: Indicates whether or not an extra choice is available for the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.
translation: Indicates whether or not an extra choice is available for the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.

english: The prompt text for an extra choice that allows the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.
translation: The prompt text for an extra choice that allows the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.

english: Indicates whether or not the dialog is currently being used by one or more players.
translation: Indicates whether or not the dialog is currently being used by one or more players.

english: The chat message that is displayed to the player when they first activate the dialog.
translation: The chat message that is displayed to the player when they first activate the dialog.

english: Describes the purpose of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant icon on the dialog's activation button.
translation: Describes the purpose of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant icon on the dialog's activation button.

english: Describes the tone of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant color in the dialog interface.
translation: Describes the tone of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant color in the dialog interface.

english: Indicates how the dialog may be used by players. Use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer if only one player should interact with the dialog at a time, otherwise use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers.
translation: Indicates how the dialog may be used by players. Use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer if only one player should interact with the dialog at a time, otherwise use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers.

english: Returns an array of the players currently conversing with this dialog.
translation: Returns an array of the players currently conversing with this dialog.

english: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players
translation: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players

english: A UnionOperation is a union of multiple parts
translation: A UnionOperation is a union of multiple parts

english: Override the colors of the mesh with the part color.
translation: Override the colors of the mesh with the part color.

english: A NegateOperation can be used to create holes in other parts
